<refentry id="MGR-RESETGTM">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>RESET GTM</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>Manage - Language Statements</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>RESET GTM</refname>
    <refpurpose>reset specified parameters of pg_settings view to default</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <indexterm zone="mgr-resetgtm">
    <primary>RESET GTM</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>
RESET GTM ALL ( parameter [, ...] ) [ FORCE ] 
RESET GTM { MASTER | SLAVE | EXTRA } <replaceable class="parameter">node_name</replaceable> ( parameter [, ...] ) [ FORCE ]

<phrase>where <replaceable class="parameter">parameter</replaceable> can be one of:</phrase>

     the parameter that in the file of postgres.conf and alse belong to the view of pg_settings.
</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>
<command>RESET GTM</command> reset the value of parameter to the default and the parameter which is own to the file of postgres.conf,it's also belong to the view of pg_settings;the operator won't check the the value and name of parameter correctly if adding 'force' at the tail of command line,in addition,it will update param table.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">Parameter</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The parameter that in the file of postgres.conf and alse belong to the view of pg_settings.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <para>
      Reset the value of 'synchronous_commit' and 'max_wal_senders' to the default:
<programlisting>
reset gtm master gtm_master(synchronous_commit, max_wal_senders);
</programlisting>
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>See Also</title>

    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member><xref linkend="mgr-setgtm"></member>
    </simplelist>
  </refsect1>

</refentry>
